trans-unit.source: Provides access to the property values of a <see cref="T:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern" /> object using its <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.TransformPattern.Current" /> or <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.TransformPattern.Cached" /> accessors.
trans-unit.target: Proporciona acceso a los valores de propiedades de un objeto <see cref="T:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern" /> mediante sus descriptores de acceso <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.TransformPattern.Current" /> o <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.TransformPattern.Cached" />.

trans-unit.source: Gets a value that specifies whether the value of a [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element is read-only.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene un valor que especifica si el valor de un elemento [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] es de solo lectura.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if the value is read-only; <see langword="false" /> if it can be modified.
trans-unit.target: <see langword="true" /> si el valor es de solo lectura; <see langword="false" /> si se puede modificar.

trans-unit.source: The default is <see langword="true" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es <see langword="true" />.

trans-unit.source: A control should have its <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.IsEnabledProperty> set to `true` and its <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ValuePattern.IsReadOnlyProperty> set to `false` prior to the creation of a <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> object.
trans-unit.target: Un control debe tener su <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement.IsEnabledProperty> establecido en `true` y su <xref:System.Windows.Automation.ValuePattern.IsReadOnlyProperty> establecido en `false` antes de la creación de un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> objeto.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, an <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> that supports the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> control pattern has its value incremented or decremented by the control-specific <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange%2A> value.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> que admita la <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> patrón de control tiene su valor aumenta o disminuye por específico del control <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange%2A> valor.

trans-unit.source: Gets the control-specific large-change value which is added to or subtracted from the <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.Provider.IRangeValueProvider.Value" /> property.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el valor de cambio grande específico del control que se suma o se resta a la propiedad <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.Provider.IRangeValueProvider.Value" />.

trans-unit.source: The large-change value or <see langword="null" /> if the element does not support <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange" />.
trans-unit.target: Valor de cambio grande o <see langword="null" /> si el elemento no admite <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange" />.

trans-unit.source: The default value is 0.0.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es 0.0.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, an <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> that supports the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> control pattern has its value incremented or decremented by the control-specific <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange%2A> value.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> que admita la <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> patrón de control tiene su valor aumenta o disminuye por específico del control <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.LargeChange%2A> valor.

trans-unit.source: Gets the maximum range value supported by the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el valor máximo del intervalo que el elemento [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] admite.

trans-unit.source: The maximum value supported by the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element or <see langword="null" /> if the element does not support <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Maximum" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor máximo admitido por el [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elemento o <see langword="null" /> si el elemento no admite <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Maximum" />.

trans-unit.source: The default value is 0.0.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es 0.0.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, an <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> that supports the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> control pattern has its value set to the control-specific maximum value.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> que admite el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> patrón de control tiene su valor establecido en el valor máximo específico del control.

trans-unit.source: Gets the minimum range value supported by the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el valor mínimo del intervalo que el elemento [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] admite.

trans-unit.source: The minimum value supported by the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element or <see langword="null" /> if the element does not support <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Minimum" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor mínimo admitido por el [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elemento o <see langword="null" /> si el elemento no admite <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Minimum" />.

trans-unit.source: The default value is 0.0.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es 0.0.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, an <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> that supports the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> control pattern has its value set to the control-specific minimum value.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> que admite el <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> patrón de control tiene su valor establecido en el valor mínimo de específica del control.

trans-unit.source: Gets the small-change value, unique to the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element, which is added to or subtracted from the elements <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Value" /> property.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el valor de cambio pequeño, único para el elemento de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)], que se suma a la propiedad <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Value" /> de los elementos o se resta de ella.

trans-unit.source: The small-change value unique to the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element or <see langword="null" /> if the element does not support <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.SmallChange" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor de cambio pequeño único para la [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elemento o <see langword="null" /> si el elemento no admite <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.SmallChange" />.

trans-unit.source: The default value is 0.0.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es 0.0.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, an <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> that supports the <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> control pattern has its value incremented or decremented by the control-specific <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.SmallChange%2A> value.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.AutomationElement> que admita la <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> patrón de control tiene su valor aumenta o disminuye por específico del control <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.SmallChange%2A> valor.

trans-unit.source: Gets the current value of the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el valor actual del elemento de [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)].

trans-unit.source: The current value of the [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] element or <see langword="null" /> if the element does not support <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Value" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor actual de la [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_uiautomation](~/includes/tla2sharptla-uiautomation-md.md)] elemento o <see langword="null" /> si el elemento no admite <see cref="P:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern.RangeValuePatternInformation.Value" />.

trans-unit.source: The default value is 0.0.
trans-unit.target: El valor predeterminado es 0.0.

trans-unit.source: In the following example, a <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> object obtained from a target control is passed into a function that retrieves the current <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> property values.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo siguiente, un <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> objeto obtenido de un control de destino se pasa a una función que recupera actual <xref:System.Windows.Automation.RangeValuePattern> valores de propiedad.
